1
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:57,880
Okay.

2
00:00:58,280 --> 00:00:59,600
Have a safe trip.

3
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:12,120
Last year,

4
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,160
I went back to Hubei

5
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,760
and passed by your house.

6
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,289
The door lock was all rusty.

7
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,400
It's been so many years.

8
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:21,200
You haven't been back, have you?

9
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:26,840
Just now,

10
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,560
Uncle Yin wasn't in a rush to find you a job.

11
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:32,160
Xinjiang

12
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,200
is different from other places.

13
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:37,200
The people here are simple and kind.

14
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:45,360
If you live here long enough,

15
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,890
your heart will find peace.

16
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,160
Uncle Yin hopes you can be happy.

17
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,039
Let me tell you the truth.

18
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,680
It's useless for me to go.

19
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,840
A remote village with no free shipping

20
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,440
can't sustain a livestream.

21
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:03,560
I know you won't go with me.

22
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,600
You have something on your mind.

23
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:10,919
There was a team-building sticker on your suitcase.

24
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:12,580
I saw you secretly tear it off.

25
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,079
Traveling should be fun.

26
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:22,560
You must have encountered something unbearable.

27
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,440
What a pity.

28
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,600
The beautiful scenery of Xinjiang,

29
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,480
you probably didn't have time to enjoy it then.

30
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,640
It's okay.

31
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,620
We are on the main road of the county town now.

32
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:34,980
You can take a look.

33
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:49,890
What do you think

34
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,800
would happen if I stayed?

35
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,170
It would be very different.

36
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,000
If you need anything in the future,

37
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,130
you can just tell me.

38
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,080
This is Grandpa Bate's house.

39
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:09,440
But it's fine.

40
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,980
He's usually not here.

41
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,460
He travels with the flock.

42
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:16,210
The lights in our village haven't been fixed yet.

43
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:18,600
There might be wild animals around.

44
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:20,560
Wild animals?

45
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,890
You don't have to sugarcoat it.

46
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,440
Just say it.

47
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,520
It's fine.

48
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:29,010
They usually don't come into the village.

49
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,320
About me coming back with you,

50
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,600
I think I was a bit impulsive.

51
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:36,090
Since you're here, just settle in.

52
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,540
Get a good sleep first.

53
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,120
I think...

54
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,320
I already told Mr. Yin

55
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,200
that you are staying.

56
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,640
He was really happy.

57
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:43,720
He said the two of us

58
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,250
are his proudest students.

59
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,200
I...

60
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:47,960
No, I...

61
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:48,720
Alright.

62
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,160
Just get a good sleep first.

63
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:50,920
I'm leaving.

64
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:56,570
I'm leaving now.

65
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,280
Oh, Ren Zhen.

66
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,200
Just accept your fate.

67
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,880
Remember when you go out,

68
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,340
you must use a flashlight.

69
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,050
Don't worry. I won't step out of this door.

70
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,600
There are so many stars here.

71
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,600
How am I supposed to sleep here?

72
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,200
Is this Jiao Li's girlfriend?

73
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:28,600
Yes.

74
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,200
Yesterday my dad asked Jiao Li to bring back rubber shoes.

75
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,060
But he brought back a girlfriend!

76
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:34,480
But why did Jiao Li

77
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,120
let his girlfriend stay here?

78
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,920
Because his girlfriend snores.

79
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,840
I don't snore.

80
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,520
Then who are you?

81
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,600
I was invited by him

82
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,080
to lead your village to wealth.

83
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:49,480
I can barely be considered half an expert.

84
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,640
The experts on TV all have full beards.

85
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,000
Sister, why are you so pretty?

86
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,360
Flatterer.

87
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,800
You must be Ayijiang.

88
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,300
You must be Ruozha.

89
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,800
Do you ride camels to school?

90
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:04,540
Are you born knowing how to twist your necks?

91
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,160
Why are you here?

92
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,640
Jiaoli, save us!

93
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,360
What's wrong?

94
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,440
They were peeking through my window.

95
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:15,700
We were having a friendly conversation.

96
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,360
All right. Let's have breakfast first.

97
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,200
Thank you.

98
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,530
Then go somewhere with me after we finish.

99
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,600
Our Xiacun Village

100
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,280
has a total of 437 people.

101
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:30,080
The total arable land area of the village is 1,300 mu.

102
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,409
Every household raises cattle and sheep,

103
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,490
and also plants some wolfberries.

104
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,600
Party Secretary,

105
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,970
these are raisins sun-dried by my family.

106
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:38,960
Thank you. Okay, thanks.

107
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,400
You're welcome.

108
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,080
Even so,

109
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,760
the average annual income of the villagers

110
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,280
is only around 15,000.

111
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,000
It is not wealthy,

112
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,880
just barely enough to make ends meet.

113
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,280
Compared with other surrounding villages,

114
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,540
it's still far behind.

115
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,000
Party Secretary.

116
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,240
These are crabapples I just picked this morning.

117
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,080
Have a taste.

118
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,040
Okay. Thank you.

119
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,570
I'll leave you to your work.

120
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:05,160
I spent a long time

121
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,760
thoroughly investigating the situation in Xiacun Village.

122
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,080
I think live-streaming e-commerce

123
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:09,920
is indeed worth a try.

124
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,960
Party Secretary, this is a pumpkin I just picked.

125
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:12,720
For you.

126
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,760
Thank you.

127
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,040
How is it?

128
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,240
The people of Xiacun Village are hospitable, right?

129
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,970
Let's go. I'll show you around.

130
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,280
This is our village committee.

131
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:22,840
Let's go.

132
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,320
And this

133
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,880
is our cooperative.

134
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,159
It's so big.

135
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:35,240
Isn't it?

136
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,360
Come, over there.

137
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,880
Let's take a look.

138
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,760
Not bad.

139
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,040
Your equipment is quite complete.

140
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,260
Mr. Yin taught me a saying:

141
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:55,640
A workman must first sharpen his tools

142
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,100
if he is to do his work well.

143
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,380
I want everyone to know

144
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,600
what live streaming is,

145
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,800
and then decide what to stream and sell.

146
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,650
Have you thought this through?

147
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,860
I want you to take a look

148
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:07,680
and see if this plan is feasible.

149
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:09,800
Since I am the Secretary of Xia Village,

150
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,800
I have the responsibility

151
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,660
and obligation

152
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,290
to help everyone live well,

153
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:14,530
better than before,

154
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,660
even if it's just a little bit better.

155
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,400
Farming

156
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:18,570
and herding,

157
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,000
I am not good at.

158
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,080
But these

159
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,240
are my new farming tools.

160
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:24,440
Live streaming to help farmers

161
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,680
is my new farm work.

162
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,160
Ren Zhen,

163
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,280
join me.

164
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,260
Is this the glorious charm of our Secretary?

165
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,240
This light gets pretty hot after a while.

166
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,560
When streaming in the future, we must think about

167
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,890
how to cool things down.

168
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,760
E-commerce is all about

169
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,600
people, goods, and locations.

170
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:49,360
With this professional equipment and team,

171
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,720
we can barely be considered

172
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,880
a startup model.

173
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,120
But what about the goods?

174
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:56,120
Mr. Secretary, what are we selling?

175
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,860
I'll keep you in suspense for now.

176
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,960
Jiao Li, Ren Zhen.

177
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:02,680
Dad Yin.

178
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,920
You're here, Mr. Yin.

179
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,620
One of my students lives here.

180
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,960
I just finished a home visit,

181
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:09,560
so I dropped by to see you two.

182
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,620
You're fitting in quite well.

183
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,040
Mr. Yin,

184
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,440
I plan to take Ren Zhen

185
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,240
to Aunt Guli's farmland later.

186
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,540
Have you figured out what to sell?

187
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:22,480
Good.

188
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,360
I'll leave you two to it.

189
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,160
Bate's nephew is going

190
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:28,210
to take me back to the county later.

191
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,640
Then we'll walk you to the village entrance.

192
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,600
Let's go.

193
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,730
Is she settling in okay?

194
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,610
I was worried last night

195
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:39,200
when she suddenly left with her suitcase.

196
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:41,200
I thought something happened to her.

197
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:41,720
No.

198
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,520
I have to go.

199
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,320
I can't even get a location for a taxi.

200
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,840
Am I supposed to hike in the dark?

201
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,520
Oh my god.

202
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,000
Why did I go with him?

203
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,800
Just because he's a bit handsome?

204
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,560
Ren Zhen.

205
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,160
You'll stumble one day.

206
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:54,240
How can we sleep?

207
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,490
I didn't expect it. I know my students.

208
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,840
Ren Zhen works very seriously.

209
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,200
Once she promises something,

210
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,730
she will not easily give up.

211
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,960
I believe what the teacher said.

212
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,040
Jiao Li, Jiao Li.

213
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,360
Jiao Li, Jiao Li.

214
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:16,240
Grandpa Bate's sheep are missing.
